2ï¸âƒ£ Why Each Component is Added
âœ… HAProxy (Load Balancer)

Ensures high availability by distributing incoming traffic across backend servers.

Prevents overloading one server, improving performance.

Can detect failures and redirect requests to healthy servers.

âœ… Two Backend Servers

Redundancy: If one server fails, the second handles traffic.

Scalability: Multiple servers manage more user requests efficiently.

âœ… Primary-Replica Database Setup (Master-Slave)

Primary (Master) Database: Handles read/write operations.

Replica (Slave) Database: Handles read-only requests for load balancing.

Why? Improves performance by distributing database queries.

3ï¸âƒ£ Load Balancer Configuration & Algorithms
ğŸ”¹ Distribution Algorithm
Your HAProxy can be configured with different algorithms:

Round Robin â†’ Requests are distributed equally across servers.

Least Connections â†’ Sends requests to the server with the fewest active connections.

Source Hash â†’ Ensures consistent requests go to the same server.

ğŸ”¹ Active-Active vs. Active-Passive Setup
Active-Active â†’ Both backend servers handle requests simultaneously.

Active-Passive â†’ One server is active, while the other is standby and takes over if the active one fails.

Which to Choose?

Active-Active is ideal for high-performance scaling.

Active-Passive is safer but limits resource utilization.

4ï¸âƒ£ How Primary-Replica (Master-Slave) Databases Work
The Primary (Master) database is responsible for all write operations.

The Replica (Slave) database is used only for read requests to reduce the load.

If the Master fails, the Replica can be promoted to become the new Master.

ğŸ”¹ Difference for the application:

The application writes to the Primary.

The application reads from the Replica to improve performance.

5ï¸âƒ£ Issues with This Infrastructure
ğŸ”´ Single Points of Failure (SPOF)
HAProxy failure â†’ If the load balancer fails, the entire system becomes inaccessible.

Single Primary Database â†’ If the master database crashes, writes are blocked.

ğŸ”´ Security Issues
No firewall â†’ Makes the system vulnerable to attacks.

No HTTPS â†’ Leaves connections unencrypted.

ğŸ”´ No Monitoring
No system in place to track performance or detect failures.

6ï¸âƒ£ Improvements to Address These Issues
âœ… Deploy multiple HAProxy instances â†’ Avoid SPOF. âœ… Use HTTPS with SSL/TLS â†’ Encrypt data. âœ… Add firewall rules â†’ Protect against attacks. âœ… Set up monitoring tools â†’ Track system health.